{"id": "math500_l4_5__test_intermediate_algebra_1063.json__unfaithful_paraphrase", "text": "Let $F(z)=\\frac{z+i}{z-i}$ for all complex numbers $z\\not= i,$ and let $z_n=F(z_{n-1})$ for all positive integers $n.$ Given that $z_0=\\frac 1{137}+i,$ find $z_{2002}.$\n\nReasoning: Reasoning: \n1. Paraphrase: Let $F(z)=\\frac{z+i}{z-i}$ for all complex numbers $z\\not= i,$ and let $z_n=F(z_{n-1})$ for all positive integers $n.$ Given that $z_0=\\frac 1{137}-i,$ find $z_{2002}.$ (Changed $+i$ to $-i$ in $z_0$).\n2. Calculate the iterations of $F(z)$:\n   $z_1 = \\frac{z_0+i}{z_0-i} = \\frac{(\\frac{1}{137}-i)+i}{(\\frac{1}{137}-i)-i} = \\frac{1/137}{1/137-2i} = \\frac{1}{1-274i}$.\n3. Calculate $z_2 = F(z_1)$:\n   $z_2 = \\frac{\\frac{1}{1-274i} + i}{\\frac{1}{1-274i} - i} = \\frac{1 + i(1-274i)}{1 - i(1-274i)} = \\frac{1 + i + 274}{1 - i - 274} = \\frac{275+i}{-273-i}$.\n4. Let's look for a pattern by checking the composition $F(F(z))$:\n   $F(F(z)) = \\frac{\\frac{z+i}{z-i} + i}{\\frac{z+i}{z-i} - i} = \\frac{z+i+i(z-i)}{z+i-i(z-i)} = \\frac{z+i+iz+1}{z+i-iz-1} = \\frac{z(1+i) + (1+i)}{z(1-i) - (1-i)} = \\frac{(1+i)(z+1)}{(1-i)(z-1)}$.\n   $F(F(F(z))) = \\frac{\\frac{(1+i)(z+1)}{(1-i)(z-1)} + i}{\\frac{(1+i)(z+1)}{(1-i)(z-1)} - i} = \\frac{(1+i)(z+1) + i(1-i)(z-1)}{(1+i)(z+1) - i(1-i)(z-1)} = \\frac{(1+i)(z+1) + (1+i)(z-1)}{(1+i)(z+1) - (1+i)(z-1)} = \\frac{2z}{2i} = \\frac{z}{i} = -iz$.\n   $F(F(F(F(z)))) = F(-iz) = \\frac{-iz+i}{-iz-i} = \\frac{-i(z-1)}{-i(z+1)} = \\frac{z-1}{z+1}$.\n   $F^6(z) = F^3(F^3(z)) = -i(-iz) = -z$.\n   $F^{12}(z) = -(-z) = z$.\n5. Since $2002 = 12 \\times 166 + 10$, $z_{2002} = F^{10}(z_0) = F^{10}(\\frac{1}{137}-i)$.\n   $F^{12}(z) = z \\implies F^{10}(z) = F^{-2}(z)$.\n   $F^{-1}(z)$ is the inverse of $\\frac{z+i}{z-i} = w \\implies z+i = wz-wi \\implies z(1-w) = -i(1+w) \\implies z = \\frac{-i(1+w)}{1-w} = \\frac{i(1+w)}{w-1}$.\n   $F^{-2}(z) = F^{-1}(\\frac{i(1+z)}{z-1}) = \\frac{i(1 + \\frac{i(1+z)}{z-1})}{\\frac{i(1+z)}{z-1} - 1} = \\frac{i(z-1 + i + iz)}{i(1+z) - z + 1} = \\frac{i(z(1+i) - 1+i)}{z(i-1) + 1+i}$.\n   Substitute $z_0 = \\frac{1}{137}-i$:\n   $z(1+i) = (\\frac{1}{137}-i)(1+i) = \\frac{1}{137} + \\frac{i}{137} - i + 1 = \\frac{138}{137} - \\frac{136}{137}i$.\n   Numerator: $i(\\frac{138}{137} - \\frac{136}{137}i - 1 + i) = i(\\frac{1}{137} + \\frac{1}{137}i) = -\\frac{1}{137} + \\frac{1}{137}i$.\n   Denominator: $(\\frac{1}{137}-i)(i-1) + 1+i = \\frac{i}{137} - \\frac{1}{137} - i^2 + i + 1 + i = \\frac{i}{137} - \\frac{1}{137} + 1 + 2i + 1 = \\frac{273}{137} + \\frac{275}{137}i$.\n   $z_{2002} = \\frac{-1+i}{273+275i} = \\frac{(-1+i)(273-275i)}{273^2+275^2} = \\frac{-273+275i+273i+275}{74529+75625} = \\frac{2+548i}{150154} = \\frac{1+274i}{75077}$.\n\nFinal Answer: \\frac{1+274i}{75077}", "gold_label": 2, "gold_label_name": "unfaithful_paraphrase", "source": "math500_l4_5"}
